President Donald Trump has proclaimed October 2019 as National Disability Employment Awareness Month. The proclamation highlights the contributions of Americans with disabilities to the workforce and emphasizes the importance of creating an inclusive environment for them to participate in the economy. The Trump administration is working to expand opportunities for individuals with disabilities through apprenticeships and initiatives that promote workforce inclusion. The proclamation also acknowledges the role of employers in promoting workplace access for individuals with disabilities and encourages federal contractors to take proactive steps in recruiting, hiring, and advancing people with disabilities. The proclamation concludes with a call for government leaders, employers, and the American people to recognize National Disability Employment Awareness Month through appropriate programs and activities.